Program: Discovery
Title: Lake Vostok
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxhr
Last Broadcast Date: 08 October 1999
A report on Lake Vostok, Antarctica, the world's most remote area of fresh water. The lake was discovered by accident and gets its name from being located under the Russian Vostok station. We know it is 1km deep and sits under 4km of ice. It is one of the world's great landmarks.